  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use this lesson when you can already describe pure functions and immutability and are ready to learn how functional programs combine small functions into larger ones.\n¶First-class functions Before functions can be composed, they must be values. A first-class function is a function that a language treats like any other value — it can be stored in a variable, passed as an argument, and returned as a result.\n",
